  "texts": [
    "Our results are further bolstered by their preservation under a different binning procedure (Supplementary Fig. 6C-E).",
    "Thus, coarse positions along a linear track can be best distinguished during dense theta phases, in agreement with our model.",
    "Note that we always consider 4 bins at a time even for track scales smaller than 1/4, because changing the number of bins across scales introduces a bias in the shuffled data (Supplementary Fig. 6F-H).",
    "At finer scales, this process sometimes fails to capture entire fields and artificially splits them (Fig. 6C, left).",
    "Here, we adopt a neutral approach and do not adjust our partitions to avoid these cases; the opposite approach was adopted in Fig. 5 where intact fields were explicitly extracted."
